According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Electric Micro Gripper Market was valued at USD 42 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 45.6 million in 2025 to USD 73.7 million by 2031, registering a CAGR of 8.4% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing robust growth due to the increasing adoption of industrial automation, rising demand for miniaturized electronic components, and advancements in robotics, semiconductor manufacturing, and medical devices. Electric micro grippers are gaining popularity for their superior precision, programmable force control, and clean operation, making them essential for high-accuracy applications across multiple industries.
